9
00:00:52,787 --> 00:00:56,922
the delorean sports car was  
manufactured in northern ireland

10
00:00:56,924 --> 00:00:58,858
in the early 1980s.      

11
00:00:58,860 --> 00:01:02,395
with gull-wing doors and brushed
stainless steel panels,    

12
00:01:02,397 --> 00:01:05,130
the delorean was known for its flashy style.     

13
00:01:05,132 --> 00:01:08,401
today, many of these cars are in rough shape,        

14
00:01:08,403 --> 00:01:12,471
but a restoration can make a delorean look like new.   

15
00:01:12,473 --> 00:01:14,607
♪♪         

16
00:01:14,609 --> 00:01:19,412
this delorean is a rare relic from the '80s.         

17
00:01:19,414 --> 00:01:24,883
only 9,080 of these iconic cars
were manufactured.       

18
00:01:24,885 --> 00:01:27,753
no longer operational, this delorean         

19
00:01:27,755 --> 00:01:29,888
might have been destined for the junk yard.       

20
00:01:29,890 --> 00:01:32,090
but with professional restoration,   

21
00:01:32,092 --> 00:01:37,096
this company has the spare parts
to get it up and running.   

22
00:01:37,098 --> 00:01:40,165
the process starts with the diagnostics.        

23
00:01:40,167 --> 00:01:43,035
the technician examines the suspension,        

24
00:01:43,037 --> 00:01:45,104
the steering rack, and brakes. 

25
00:01:45,106 --> 00:01:47,973
he finds significant deterioration   

26
00:01:47,975 --> 00:01:50,576
and documents his findings.  

27
00:01:50,578 --> 00:01:53,579
he scrutinizes every part of the old delorean      

28
00:01:53,581 --> 00:01:58,718
and produces an 11-page report on its condition.       

29
00:01:58,720 --> 00:02:01,320
once all the problems have been identified,     

30
00:02:01,322 --> 00:02:03,656
the mechanic gets to work,   

31
00:02:03,658 --> 00:02:06,525
removing plugs to drain some of the coolant.      

32
00:02:06,527 --> 00:02:09,528
he disassembles many pipes and hoses      

33
00:02:09,530 --> 00:02:15,468
that run coolant from the radiator to the rear engine.  

34
00:02:15,470 --> 00:02:18,471
many of the coolant pipes will need to be cleaned    

35
00:02:18,473 --> 00:02:20,206
in order to be re-used.    

36
00:02:20,208 --> 00:02:22,274
the rubber hoses can't be salvaged       

37
00:02:22,276 --> 00:02:24,543
and will need replacement.   

38
00:02:24,545 --> 00:02:27,213
the mechanic disassembles the brakes.          

39
00:02:27,215 --> 00:02:31,817
the calipers are in bad shape but can be rebuilt.      

40
00:02:31,819 --> 00:02:34,419
the rusty rotors are still thick enough     

41
00:02:34,421 --> 00:02:37,223
that they can be resurfaced.  

42
00:02:37,225 --> 00:02:40,493
after mounting new tires    

43
00:02:40,495 --> 00:02:43,162
and refinishing the cast alloy wheels,     

44
00:02:43,164 --> 00:02:46,732
another technician bolts them to the hubs.    

45
00:02:46,734 --> 00:02:51,036
he lowers the hoist and sets the car on the floor. 

46
00:02:51,038 --> 00:02:56,241
he tightens the lug nuts to the final torque setting.  

47
00:02:56,243 --> 00:02:58,711
a technician begins disassembling      

48
00:02:58,713 --> 00:03:00,512
the rear drive engine.     

49
00:03:00,514 --> 00:03:03,182
in order to know what needs to be replaced,   

50
00:03:03,184 --> 00:03:06,184
the technician must take the engine apart.  

51
00:03:06,186 --> 00:03:08,587
he removes the air filter box 

52
00:03:08,589 --> 00:03:11,323
in order to access the intake manifold.      

53
00:03:11,325 --> 00:03:14,793
then he unbolts the "w"-shaped manifold pipe  

54
00:03:14,795 --> 00:03:18,196
that splits the air flow to the engine.         

55
00:03:18,198 --> 00:03:22,401
once it's off, he removes the air-mixture control unit, 

56
00:03:22,403 --> 00:03:25,270
which needs restored to work. 

57
00:03:25,272 --> 00:03:27,273
with the unit out of the way, 

58
00:03:27,275 --> 00:03:31,276
he can easily get to other parts
that need replacing or fixing. 

59
00:03:31,278 --> 00:03:35,614
those include spark plugs, wires, vacuum lines,      

60
00:03:35,616 --> 00:03:38,484
the distributor cap, and rotor.

61
00:03:38,486 --> 00:03:41,086
under the front hood, the mechanic          

62
00:03:41,088 --> 00:03:43,489
pulls the fuel pump out of the gas tank        

63
00:03:43,491 --> 00:03:45,491
to check for deterioration.  

64
00:03:45,493 --> 00:03:47,226
it's beyond repair.      

65
00:03:47,228 --> 00:03:51,096
he drains any fuel the remains in the tank.    

66
00:03:51,098 --> 00:03:54,566
after the gas tank has been emptied and cleaned,      

67
00:03:54,568 --> 00:03:57,503
he inserts a new, modern-style pump module.          

68
00:03:57,505 --> 00:04:01,040
another technician holds the top of the pump down    

69
00:04:01,042 --> 00:04:05,177
as the module is clamped into place.          

70
00:04:05,179 --> 00:04:09,648
next, the technician removes the interior door panels    

71
00:04:09,650 --> 00:04:15,321
and uses a central tester to operate the power windows. 

72
00:04:15,323 --> 00:04:18,523
he confirms the power windows are functional.        

73
00:04:18,525 --> 00:04:21,460
he also checks the power locks and mirrors  

74
00:04:21,462 --> 00:04:25,331
to verify that they're working properly.   

75
00:04:25,333 --> 00:04:28,333
he pulls off exterior rubber trim.     

76
00:04:28,335 --> 00:04:31,736
he shaves off any remaining rubber bits.          

77
00:04:31,738 --> 00:04:34,272
this allows room to repair a dent        

78
00:04:34,274 --> 00:04:36,742
in the stainless steel body.  

79
00:04:36,744 --> 00:04:43,282
he files the area around the dent to remove some scratches. 

80
00:04:43,284 --> 00:04:46,418
he places a special tool over the dent.         

81
00:04:46,420 --> 00:04:50,222
it has a rod with a fine steel tip that welds to the body,  

82
00:04:50,224 --> 00:04:55,694
providing a solid grip, as he manually pulls out the dent.  

83
00:04:55,696 --> 00:04:57,830
meanwhile, another mechanic  

84
00:04:57,832 --> 00:05:00,499
applies tape to various sections of the car 

85
00:05:00,501 --> 00:05:02,034
to establish borders      

86
00:05:02,036 --> 00:05:05,437
for the refinishing of the steel body panels.   

87
00:05:05,439 --> 00:05:10,242
he sands out any imperfections or tool marks from the repairs 

88
00:05:10,244 --> 00:05:14,180
and restores the brushed finish
bumper to bumper.       

89
00:05:14,182 --> 00:05:16,381
since no paint can be used   

90
00:05:16,383 --> 00:05:19,451
to cover up repairs on bare stainless steel,    

91
00:05:19,453 --> 00:05:23,188
the body work must be done perfectly.           

92
00:05:23,190 --> 00:05:26,592
inside, technicians reupholster the seats     

93
00:05:26,594 --> 00:05:30,862
and treat any discoloration in the vinyl panels and dashboard.

94
00:05:30,864 --> 00:05:35,935
finally, the entire car gets an extensive exterior cleaning.

95
00:05:35,937 --> 00:05:39,405
it's taken months to restore this delorean,         

96
00:05:39,407 --> 00:05:43,542
but the question remains, will it run like a new car?  

97
00:05:43,544 --> 00:05:46,545
once tested in various driving conditions,      

98
00:05:46,547 --> 00:05:49,882
mechanics confirm that this 1980s throwback   

99
00:05:49,884 --> 00:05:52,651
is ready for its comeback.   

